hotel.name: Baltimore Harbor Hotel
hotel.description: In the center of the action with 360-degree views of the city skyline and an outdoor pool, the non-smoking Baltimore Harbor Hotel is a smart choice for Priceline guests. The 27-story tower houses 323 non-smoking rooms with high ceilings, desks with ample lighting and high-end ergonomic chairs, free Wi-Fi and wired internet connections and flat-panel HDTVs that you can enjoy while lounging on pillowtop beds. A free continental breakfast is served daily. The seasonal outdoor pool and sun deck, open during the summer months, are a hit with kids. There's also a roomy fitness center where the cardio machines have great vistas through floor-to-ceiling windows. Everything is within walking distance from the hotel, including the Inner Harbor, National Aquarium, 1st Mariner Arena, the Baltimore Convention Center and Johns Hopkins University. Plenty of dining options are just outside the front door. Amtrak's Penn Station is a mile north, and Baltimore/Washington Thurgood Marshall International Airport is 10 miles south. Baltimore Harbor Hotel also boasts a central location and a host of convenient amenities.

hotel.name: Excelsior Hotel
hotel.description: This Manhattan hotel is a 3-minute walk from Central Park and the 81st Street - Museum of Natural History Subway Station. It features a gym and modern rooms with a flat-screen satellite TV.An iPod docking station and a safe are included in the cream-colored rooms at Excelsior Hotel. Guests will also find ironing facilities and a hair dryer in every room. Spacious rooms with a sofa bed are available.The Excelsior Hotel offers a tour desk, which can help guests get tickets to Broadway shows. There is also a business center.The Excelsior Hotel overlooks the American Museum of Natural History and the Rose Center for Earth and Science. It is a 20-minute walk to The Metropolitan Museum of Art.

importantInfo: Please note, guests must be at least 21 years old to check in.Please note that the property exterior will be undergoing renovations Monday through Friday from 08:00 to 16:00. Guests are required to show a photo identification and credit card upon check-in. Please note that all Special Requests are subject to availability and additional charges may apply.

quotes.text: It is a beautifully maintained older/stately building, with large comfortable rooms.
Right across from Natural History Museum and half a block from Central Park
